Bottle from Mane Liquor
Pours copper color with small white head, color is amazing to look at. Nose is big on tropical notes, mainly passion fruit and mango, bit of caramel laced through. Big big flavors, tropical with caramel underlay, long length. Strong beer at 8.8%

Bottle from Mane Liquor
Very easy sessionable drinking beer. Pours light straw color with average head, light malt, biscuity flavours, summer drinking

Bottle from Mane Liquor.
Average beer. Pours light golden, no back end to speak of. Pretty sub standard

Bottle from Mane Liquor.
Had this whilst out for the Mane Liquor Staff party. Pours black with a small light brown head. Very creamy feel, dominant lactose feeling. Chocalatey notes, got better when it warmed up a bit. Definitely would love to try again

Bottle from Mane Liquor
Poured dark golden with a decent head, floral/tropical scents on the nose, decent tasting with good length, hoppy but not over powering, bit sessionable. bitter aftertaste but not too strong. Solid beer to have over Summer
